Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk
Mantralaya, Mumbai 400 032.
Date: October 20, 2025.
Reference: - 1) The Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005, dated 25.05.2006.
2) Government Notification, General Administration Department No. SRV-020 / Q. No.49 / Works.12, D. 14.07.2021
Government Orders: -
Reference No. Under Section 1, the Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delays in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005 has been promulgated.

2. Also, Reference No. 2 in the Notification of the General Administration Department, Rule No. As per 2 (2) (c), the Divisional Cadre Allocation Rules, 2021 shall not apply to the cadre of Additional Collector and Additional Collector (Selection Category).

For the purposes of the provisions of section 4 (4) and section 4 (5) of the Maharashtra Prevention of Delay in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005, the following officers of the cadre (Additional Collector) shall be appointed in front of their names in column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.

4. The aforesaid officers are being unilaterally relieved from their present working position with effect from the date 20.10.2025 (M.No) for immediate joining at the place of posting. The concerned officer should immediately inform the Government by e-mail / post at e.revenue@maharashtra.gov.in 1 as to the date on which he / she appeared at the place of new appointment.
